comment.author: 31324280@N02
comment._content: HarveNYC - Circular Quay was named as such a long time before today's present configuration. The whole "bay" was semi-circular in shape, hence the name. Of course today the ferry terminals lining the quay are indeed not  circular. I think there are old images of the area on Flickr - the Powerhouse Museums collection if I recall.
